    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People, usually priests, who makes statements prompted by his or her deity. This was especially common in ancient times, sometimes in a specific sacred place. The oracle's utterances serve as a directive to the inquiring party.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
